17/08/2010
MOSCOW, Russia -- The Federal Security Service in Moscow on Monday (August 16th) announced the arrest of a Romanian diplomat suspected of spying. 
Gabriel Grecu, first secretary in the political department of Romania's Embassy in Russia, was arrested as he allegedly tried to obtain secret military information from a Russian citizen. 
According to the security service, spy equipment was seized from Grecu. 
Authorities in Bucharest have not commented on the case. 
(AP, CNN, AFP, Hotnews.ro, Reuters, Adevarul, Romania Libera, Realitatea - 16/08/10)
